Target: `tests/AnswerPlan.Tests.ps1` (new test file if absent)

Reason:
- lock in the Priority 0 fix that `Export-AnswerTrace` must not report failure after a successful export just because unlock in `finally` throws
- verify helper fallback behavior remains non-fatal when run/workspace resolution helpers fail

---

## Patch A: add unlock-isolation regression test

```powershell
Describe "AnswerPlan Priority 0 regressions" {
    BeforeAll {
        . "$PSScriptRoot/../module/LLMWorkflow/retrieval/AnswerPlan.ps1"
    }

    It "Exports an answer trace successfully even when Unlock-File throws" {
        Mock Get-Command {
            param($Name)
            switch ($Name) {
                'Lock-File' { return @{ Name = 'Lock-File' } }
                'Unlock-File' { return @{ Name = 'Unlock-File' } }
                'Write-AtomicFile' { return @{ Name = 'Write-AtomicFile' } }
                default { return $null }
            }
        }

        Mock Lock-File {
            return @{ lock = 'ok' }
        }

        Mock Write-AtomicFile {
            param($Path, $Content, $Format)
            return $null
        }

        Mock Unlock-File {
            throw 'unlock failed'
        }

        $trace = New-AnswerTrace -Query 'test query' -AnswerMode 'direct'
        $path = Export-AnswerTrace -Trace $trace -ProjectRoot $TestDrive

        $path | Should -Not -BeNullOrEmpty
        $path | Should -Match '\.json$'
    }
}
```

Expected effect:
- fails against implementations where unlock failure in `finally` bubbles out and turns success into failure
- passes once unlock failure is downgraded to a warning

## Patch B: add helper fallback regression test

```powershell
It "Falls back cleanly when Get-CurrentWorkspace helper throws" {
    Mock Get-Command {
        param($Name)
        if ($Name -eq 'Get-CurrentWorkspace') {
            return @{ Name = 'Get-CurrentWorkspace' }
        }
        return $null
    }

    Mock Get-CurrentWorkspace {
        throw 'workspace resolution failed'
    }

    $plan = New-AnswerPlan -Query 'test query' -RetrievalProfile 'api-lookup'

    $plan.workspaceId | Should -Be 'unknown'
}
```

This locks in the intended non-fatal fallback path instead of silent or terminating helper failure.
